56 GAMERULES~
Each dice roll is scored as follows:
 
Three of a kind score 100*face value of one of the dice. If the face value is
1, then it is scored as 1000. For each extra die of the same face value, the
score is doubled. (ie. 4 6's would be 1200)
 
Single 1's and 5's score 100 and 50, respectively.
 
A straight, i.e. 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 scores 1500.
 
In order to get "on the board", you have to roll at least 300.  Until you roll
300, you cannot save your first score.  After you are on the board you may save
as little as you want.
~

