53 OBJECTRESISTANCE~
The resistance of an object against a pull/push force is determined by the
weight of an object and a few quick math formulas.
 
The base resistance of an object is equal to its weight. If an object is 
flagged "metal" it gets an initial addition of 1/5th its weight. The 
resistances then become based off the item type
 
For scrolls, notes and trash divide the resistance by 4.
For scraps and containers, divide the resistance by 2.
For pens and quills, multiply the resistance by 5/6.
For mob and pc corpses and fountains, multiply the resistance by 4.
 
If the absolute value (+/- 100 = 100) of the push value multiplied by 10 is
greater than the resistance of the object, the object will eventually be moved
by the pull/push force.
 
See also: pulltypes, pullforces
~

